Kontra Fruit Bowl bamboo and stainless steel
&lt;hr class=&quot;detail-divider&quot;&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;detail-story&quot;&gt;Designed by &lt;strong&gt;Normann Copenhagen&lt;/strong&gt;, the Kontra bowl emerged from a single formal question: what happens when two opposing materials — warm organic wood and cool industrial steel — are resolved into one object. The answer is this.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;detail-story&quot;&gt;The bamboo rim sits on a spun steel base, each half finished to its own logic. Neither disguises what it is. Together they hold the tension that makes the object worth looking at every day.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;detail-why&quot;&gt;selected because it earns its place on the counter — functional enough to use daily, considered enough to leave out always.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr class=&quot;detail-divider&quot;&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;detail-meta&quot;&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-label&quot;&gt;designer&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-value&quot;&gt;Normann Copenhagen&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-label&quot;&gt;materials&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-value&quot;&gt;bamboo, stainless steel&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-label&quot;&gt;origin&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-value&quot;&gt;Denmark&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-label&quot;&gt;made for&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;meta-value&quot;&gt;daily use, permanent display&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;detail-cta&quot;&gt; &lt;!-- Replace href with your affiliate link --&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;AFFILIATE_URL&quot; rel=&quot;noopener sponsored&quot;&gt;find it here →&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
